INTRODUCTION: Osteosarcoma is the most common primary bone tumor in children and 
young adults and appropriate chemotherapy can increase limb sparing and overall 
survival. Yet, the toxicity of chemotherapy regimens including MTX can be life 
threatening. Therefore; we tried another chemotherapy regimen for these 
patients.
METHOD AND MATERIALS: We investigated 15 patients aged 15 to 40 years old and 
used continuous infusion of cisplatin, doxorubicin intermittently with 
ifosfamide, doxorubicin as neoadjuvant chemotherapy. Percent of necrosis and 
toxicities was recorded for each patient.
