As providers of health care, we face increasing demand on our limited, indeed 
diminishing, resources. Economic appraisal of our interventions means assessing 
the trade-off between effectiveness, efficiency and equity. When rationing 
becomes inevitable, calculation of utility values is a valuable decision-making 
tool. This paper reviews objective measures of patient benefit, such as quality 
